        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When you want a custom message for a validator, you can't have already a translation for the messageKey.\r\nThe problem is in the Zend_Validate_Abstract class on line 219.\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\nif ($translator->isTranslated($messageKey)) {\r\n    $message = $translator->translate($messageKey);\r\n} else {\r\n    $message = $translator->translate($message);\r\n}\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\nWhen I want to use the Identical validator and I want to provide a custom message for the \"notSame\" error on form 1 (example: \"My custom message\"), but on form 2 I want a default message.\r\nBecause of the default message on form 2 I define a translation for \"notSame\". But now, because I translated the \"messageKey\" my custom message will not be available.\r\n\r\nI found already a ticket [#3313|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-3313] that solved this issue, but since the 1.10.6 it was reversed. I don't understand why?\r\n"
        },
